  "texts": [
    "The circle x 2 + y 2 = 4 has a radius of 2, so in polar coordinates, the region R is described by 0 ≤ r ≤ 2 and 0 ≤ θ ≤ π 4 (considering the quadrant where the region is).",
    "The integrand in polar coordinates is x 2 +y 2 = r 2.",
    "The Jacobian of the transformation from Cartesian to polar coordinates is r, so the integral becomes:",
    "R x 2 + y 2 dx dy = π 4 0 2 0 r 2 • r dr dθ = π 4 0 2 0 r 3 dr dθ.",
    "First, we integrate with respect to r: 2 0 r 3 dr = r 4 4 2 0 = 2 4 4 -0 4 4 = 16 4 = 4."
  ],
